Police are investigating the theft of medical equipment at St Mary’s Mission Hospital in Gilgil.Theatre monitors, medicine and assorted laboratory machines were last week found hidden in the hospital compound. Though no suspect has been arrested, the officers believe some of the workers from the hospital on the Nakuru-Nairobi highway were involved. Read: Nuns kick staff out of St Mary’s Mission Hospital in Lang’ata On Friday last week, armed police raided the facility to enforce a court order in which the Assumption Sisters of Nairobi took over management of the hospital. A police source said one of the workers tipped the management over a plan to transport the stolen equipment from the hospital.“The equipment had been hidden in an empty house. They have been collected and taken to Gilgil police station as part of the investigations,” said the source. Click here for the latest political news